dataIdInfo.idPurp: METRO Bus Routes - As of August 2014 Service Change. Developed for map display and analysis of route-level bus service in Geographic Information System (GIS) Software. This data is created and maintained in GIS.
dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.2.0.3348
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
One route equals one feature. "Hooked" routes are stored as 2 separate features: ie 52 Hirsch, 52 Scott. Routes are coincident with METmap - METRO's version of the Houston region STAR Map.

Changes since Previous Service Change:

Routes using N. Main St through the Hernandez Tunnel have been rerouted during construction to Washington - Houston - Crockett - Quitman. These routes include the 1 Hospital, 5 Kashmere, 9 North Main, 52 Hirsch, and 78 Irvington. The original routing on the west end of the 58 Hammerly has been modified to its original loop, but in reverse direction.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Metropolitan Transit Authority of Harris County, Texas Planning Department Division of Service Planning, Evaluation and Scheduling

report.measDesc: One feature equals one bus route. These bus routes are created in File Geodatabase format for ad will be exported to shapefile format for use in GIS. The routes are created by selecting from METRO roads layer and the route segments are then merged as one feature for each "unhooked" route. The routes are, therefore, coincident with the METRO maintained roads layer. The routes are to be used for regional analysis.
The routes may not be coincident with METRO maintained centerline street network.
